If you look into it every single corner of the world has a developed traditional "folk wrestling" style. It makes a ton of sense because there's no teeth getting knocked out or brain damage, you can test your strength against ur peers safely. Everyone used to wrestle in the past.

I think to be able to box without genuinely wanting to hurt someone requires a very advanced culture like England, I remember H.P. Lovecraft talking about often fistfighting his classmates in school and saying they did not hit each other in the face because they were gentlemen...

Lovecraft had a story ("The Statement of Randolph Carter") where a man loses his mind after merely hearing an alien voice through a telephone that really reminds you of St. Paisios saying if the devil appeared on TV everyone watching at that moment would immediately go insane.
